[00:36.01]	It best agrees with night. Come, civil night,
[00:39.95]	Thou sober-suited matron, all in black,
[00:43.49]	And learn me how to lose a winning match,
[00:47.27]	Play'd for a pair of stainless maidenhoods:
[00:51.20]	Hood my unmann'd blood, bating in my cheeks,
[00:55.14]	With thy black mantle; till strange love, grown bold,
[00:59.73]	Think true love acted simple modesty.
[01:03.18]	Come, night; come, Romeo; come, thou day in night;
